{
  "texts": [
    "To summarise this analysis, we observe that adapter models and LoRA produce comparable or even better results for sub-task 3 or in the scenarios when the training data is scarce or is only available in one language.",
    "This is a promising result given that these approaches require less memory and training time, as discussed in the previous section.",
    "The results reported in this study are limited to using one dataset annotated with different classification tasks.",
    "Further analysis would be beneficial to test these findings on a diverse set of corpora and tasks.",
    "Additionally, we examined the effect of one adapter technique, which prevents us from generalising our findings to all types of adapter methods."
  ]
}